A Tier One network is one that can reach
every other network through peering.

2
00:00:04,850 --> 00:00:08,930
A Tier Two network is one that peers
some of its network access and

3
00:00:08,930 --> 00:00:11,440
purchase some of its network access.

4
00:00:11,440 --> 00:00:15,180
A Tier Three network is one that
purchases all of the transit

5
00:00:15,180 --> 00:00:16,600
from other networks.

